@NODE CONF_INFO "Configuration Editor (information bar)"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Information Bar@{fg text}

This  textgadget will display information on every button.  This only works
when this info is in the config-file (preceeded by a semi-column ';')@{ub}

To show info, simply press any button in the window, and there it is!
@ENDNODE


@NODE CONF_NMBR "Configuration Editor (default numbers)"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Numeric Default Settings@{fg text}

The  first column of gadgets are for setting the default numeric variables.
To  change,  simply click the gadget and type a new value.  If the value is
too high it will be changed to the maximum value.  If your value is too low
or otherwise invalid, the lowest possible value will be automatically set.

1. @{fg shine}Activated Tool:@{fg text}@{ub}
Can  be  a  value ranging from 1 to 10.  On startup of the ASCII Editor the
tool with the specified number is already activated. In the information bar
you can see which tool you activate after you filled in a number. The
following tools are available:
@{fg fill}
        1 = Freehand                    6 = Draw Box    
        2 = Fill Line                   7 = Draw Ellipse
        3 = Airbrush                    8 = Paste Brush 
        4 = Pick Brush                  9 = Text Edit   
        5 = Straight Line               10= Clear       

@{b}2. @{fg shine}Activated Colour:@{fg text}@{ub}
Can  be  a  value  ranging  from  0 to 7, specifying which colour should be
active on startup.

@{b}3. @{fg shine}Project Width:@{fg text}@{ub}
The default width of the project (in characters).  The minimum value is 77,
the maximum is 250

@{b}4. @{fg shine}Project Height:@{fg text}@{ub}
The  default  height  of  the  project (the maximum nnumber of lines).  the
minumum value is 29, the maximum is 250.

@{b}5. @{fg shine}Airbrush Size:@{fg text}@{ub}
A  value  ranging  from  1  to  10  which  sets the 'size' parameter of the
Airbrush Options window in ASCII-Edit.
@ENDNODE

@NODE CONF_CYCL "Configuration Editor (cyclegadget defaults)"

@{fg shine}@{b}The Cyclegadget Defaults@{fg text}

The  second  column of gadgets are for setting the default settings of some
cyclegadgets  in  ASCII  Edit.  To change, simply click the gadget to cycle
through the options.

        @{b}@{fg shine}Default Mode:@{fg text}
        Switch between Foreground and Background@{ub}
        To set the Front/Back switch in the Tools window of ASCII-Edit.

        @{b}@{fg shine}Display:@{fg text}
        Switch between Normal and AmigaGuide@{ub}
        To set the display mode in the Options/Display menu.

        @{b}@{fg shine}Airbrush Speed:@{fg text}
        Switch betweem Fast and Slow@{ub}
        To set the Airbrush Speed switch in the Airbrush Options window.

        @{b}@{fg shine}Open Window:@{fg text}
        Cycle through No Window, Load and Init New@{ub}
        To set which window you want to be opened on startup:
        @{b}No Window@{ub} :will do nothing.
        @{b}Load@{ub}      :will open the Load window after the About requester is
                   closed.
        @{b}Init New@{ub}  :will open the Init New window after the About requester
                   is closed. This is the window you get when you select
                   the Project/New menu option.

        @{b}@{fg shine}Freehand Type:@{fg text}
